UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. David Frank TRAGER, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-10864.

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Aug. 18, 2009. Steven M. Sucsy, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office Northern District of Texas, Lubbock, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. . David Frank Trager, Spur, TX, pro se. Before HIGGINBOTHAM, DAVIS, and CLEMENT, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent David Frank Trager has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed *297a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Trager has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no non-frivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should nol be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5m Cir. R. 47.5.4.
